Wash and dry produce. Drain and rinse @corn{1}(drained and rinsed). Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and sliced), separating whites from greens. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}(roughly chopped). Quarter @lime{1}.

In a #medium bowl{}, whisk together @tempura batter mix{82%g}, @fajita spice blend{1%tablespoon}, @veggie stock concentrate{1%unit}, @cold water{1/3%cup}, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch} (2⁄3 cup cold water and 1 tsp sugar for 4 servings). Stir in corn, scallion whites, and @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup}.

> TIP: Batter should be thick but not dry; add a splash of water if needed.

Open package of @chopped chicken breast{10%oz} and drain off any excess liquid or rinse under cold water and pat dry with #paper towels{}. Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a 1/3-inch layer of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Once oil is hot enough that a drop of batter sizzles, carefully add 1 1/2-TBSP scoops of batter to pan; press down lightly with a #spoon{}. (For 4 servings, you may need to work in batches.) Cook until golden brown and crispy, ~{3-4%minutes} per side.

> TIP: If the fritters start to brown too quickly or oil splatters, lower the heat.

Transfer fritters to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}. Season with a pinch of @salt{}. Once cool enough to handle, cut fritters in half.

> Use pan used for chicken here.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Evenly fill tortillas with @smoky red pepper crema{2%tablespoon}, fritters, @pico de gallo{4%oz}(drained first), and as much @hot sauce{1%teaspoon} as you like; garnish with cilantro and scallion greens.

> Add chicken to tortillas along with fritters.

Divide tacos between plates; serve with a squeeze of lime juice and any remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.